Description: Fragment of wall of Attic black-figured pottery open vase. Inside glazed. Outside, head and shoulders of panther to right; red on neck; to right and below part of handle palmette and volute.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Temple of Aphrodite (Naukratis), Context Φ6(?) (?)
Curator's comments: This sherd is labelled in pencil Φ6 (however the two characters are obscured and unclear), designating this as coming from a context excavated within the opisthodomos of the second temple of Aphrodite, during Gardner’s excavations at Naukratis in 1885-1886.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.2202)
